Package MichaelPriest

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AFood
    This class represents the plants in the simulation that are eaten by the herbivores.
    Animal
    Abstract class that contains standard methods for the subclasses Herbivore and Carnivore.
    ARock
    This class represents the rocks in the simulation, they do not move and cannot be passed through by animals.
    Carnivore
    Subclass representing a carnivore.
    Config
    This class handles all the files used in the application, either when files are being written (saving) or read (loading).
    Herbivore
    Subclass representing a herbivore.
    JFX
    This class handles the simulation and all the animation used in the main pane.
    MainMenu
    Main class, implements the JavaFX library to create a menu to allow the user to interact with the application.
    World
    Holds collections of critical data that the simulation needs to function, including a list of herbivores, carnivores, food and rocks.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Direction
    enum class that contains values for NORTH, SOUTH, EAST and WEST.
